#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:119
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_VERTEX** = **0** --- :ref:`PackedVector3Array "
"<class_PackedVector3Array>`, :ref:`PackedVector2Array "
"<class_PackedVector2Array>`, or :ref:`Array <class_Array>` of vertex "
"positions."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:121
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_NORMAL** = **1** --- :ref:`PackedVector3Array "
"<class_PackedVector3Array>` of vertex normals."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:123
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_TANGENT** = **2** --- :ref:`PackedFloat32Array "
"<class_PackedFloat32Array>` of vertex tangents. Each element in groups of"
" 4 floats, first 3 floats determine the tangent, and the last the "
"binormal direction as -1 or 1."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:125
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_COLOR** = **3** --- :ref:`PackedColorArray "
"<class_PackedColorArray>` of vertex colors."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:127
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_TEX_UV** = **4** --- :ref:`PackedVector2Array "
"<class_PackedVector2Array>` for UV coordinates."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:129
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_TEX_UV2** = **5** --- :ref:`PackedVector2Array "
"<class_PackedVector2Array>` for second UV coordinates."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:131
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_BONES** = **6** --- :ref:`PackedFloat32Array "
"<class_PackedFloat32Array>` or :ref:`PackedInt32Array "
"<class_PackedInt32Array>` of bone indices. Each element in groups of 4 "
"floats."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:133
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_WEIGHTS** = **7** --- :ref:`PackedFloat32Array "
"<class_PackedFloat32Array>` of bone weights. Each element in groups of 4 "
"floats."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:135
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_INDEX** = **8** --- :ref:`PackedInt32Array "
"<class_PackedInt32Array>` of integers used as indices referencing "
"vertices, colors, normals, tangents, and textures. All of those arrays "
"must have the same number of elements as the vertex array. No index can "
"be beyond the vertex array size. When this index array is present, it "
"puts the function into \"index mode,\" where the index selects the "
"\\*i\\*'th vertex, normal, tangent, color, UV, etc. This means if you "
"want to have different normals or colors along an edge, you have to "
"duplicate the vertices."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:137
msgid ""
"For triangles, the index array is interpreted as triples, referring to "
"the vertices of each triangle. For lines, the index array is in pairs "
"indicating the start and end of each line."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_arraymesh.rst:139
msgid ""
"**ARRAY_MAX** = **9** --- Represents the size of the :ref:`ArrayType "
"<enum_ArrayMesh_ArrayType>` enum."
msgstr ""

